cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to generate aspect hierarchies from reviews. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves graph analysis, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of unsupervised techniques and sentiment analysis models suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on sentiment analysis and aspect granularity could also place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
